    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect MCS selection due to get_softmodem_function returning \"???\" \n\n### Summary\nThe `get_softmodem_function()` in softmodem-common.c could return \"???\" when multiple softmodem function bits were set or when no function bits were set. This caused downstream code that depended on the function type to make incorrect assumptions about the modem configuration, leading to MCS selection that didn't match the actual channel quality or UE capabilities.\n\nThe issue was particularly noticeable when running in configurations where scope functionality was enabled alongside normal gNB operation, causing both SOFTMODEM_GNB_BIT and SOFTMODEM_DOSCOPE_BIT to be set simultaneously.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain load conditions with telnet server active, users observed significantly lower than expected throughput and higher BLER. Tracing showed that the MCS index selected for UEs was consistently lower than expected given the measured CQI values.\n\nThe issue could be reproduced by:\n1. Starting nr-softmodem with --rfsim and --sa flags\n2. Enabling telnet server functionality \n3. Connecting a UE that reports high CQI values\n4. Observing that scheduled MCS remains low despite good channel conditions\n\n### Changes\n- `executables/softmodem-common.c`: Modified `get_softmodem_function()` to return the first matching function name when multiple bits are set, and return \"unknown\" when no bits are set, instead of returning \"???\" in both cases.\n"
}